This place is right around the corner from my work and so it’s kind of a bummer that the summer is almost over and I only just discovered it.  While the food is delicious (the al pastor is a bit spicy though), I had some personal experiences with it thag pushed it over the edge.  First off, Michael gave me compliments for finding this place, and getting his approval is more difficult than successfully invading Russia in the winter.  Secondly, I bought 99 cent gummy bears, which they happily took my dollar for and didn’t charge an annoying tax so that was a big plus.  Finally, they have those mango drink that I really like and made Michael rather perturbed, another big positive.  Overall: 5/5, yum yum.
